HEADWORD: Overwrought
<hw>O`ver*wrought</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <mord>from
<er>Overwork</er></mord>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wrought upon excessively;
overworked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Extremely agitated or excited; overexcited; -- of
